<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE gxl SYSTEM "http://gin.univ-mrs.fr/GINsim/GINML_2_1.dtd">
<gxl xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
	<graph id="mechanistic_cellular" class="regulatory" nodeorder="Dpp Grk Br_adj Aos_ext Rho_ext dpERK Mirr Pnt Rho Aos Br S X A earlyGrk Mid earlyDpp">
<node id="earlyGrk" maxvalue="1" input="true">
  <annotation>
    <comment>Gurken is a TGF-α like protein secreted by the oocyte. in early stages, it is located in the posterior pole (Neuman-Silberberg and Schupbach, 1994; Neuman-Silberberg and Schupbach, 1996)</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="357" y="70" width="70" height="25" backgroundColor="#999900" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="X" maxvalue="1">
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Br_adj:X" val="1"/>
  <value val="1">
    <exp str="!Br &amp; Br_adj"/>
  </value>
  <annotation>
    <comment>Hypothetical mechanism. EGFR activity seems to be enhanced in cells in contact with the roof region ("spectacles-shaped" pattern in Peri et al., 1999, Nakamura et al., 2003, Zartman et al., 2009). Br is taken as a marker of the roof.

Moreover, Rho is expressed along the high-Notch side of a high/low Notch border; ectopic rho expression may be induced by ectopic high/low Notch barriers generated by Notch- clones (Ward et al., 2006).</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="462" y="588" width="35" height="25" backgroundColor="#cccccc" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="Rho_ext" maxvalue="2" input="true">
  <annotation>
    <comment>Denotes Rho expression in neighboring cells.</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<rect x="650" y="490" width="60" height="25" backgroundColor="#ffffff" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="dpERK" maxvalue="2">
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Grk:dpERK:3" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Grk:dpERK:3 X:dpERK" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Grk:dpERK:3 S:dpERK:1" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Grk:dpERK:3 S:dpERK:1 X:dpERK" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Grk:dpERK:3 S:dpERK:2" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Grk:dpERK:3 S:dpERK:2 X:dpERK" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" A:dpERK Grk:dpERK:3" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" A:dpERK Grk:dpERK:3 X:dpERK" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" A:dpERK Grk:dpERK:3 S:dpERK:1" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" A:dpERK Grk:dpERK:3 S:dpERK:1 X:dpERK" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" A:dpERK Grk:dpERK:3 S:dpERK:2" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" A:dpERK Grk:dpERK:3 S:dpERK:2 X:dpERK" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Grk:dpERK:2 X:dpERK" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Grk:dpERK:2 S:dpERK:1 X:dpERK" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Grk:dpERK:2 S:dpERK:2" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Grk:dpERK:2 S:dpERK:2 X:dpERK" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" A:dpERK Grk:dpERK:2 X:dpERK" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" A:dpERK Grk:dpERK:2 S:dpERK:1 X:dpERK" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" A:dpERK Grk:dpERK:2 S:dpERK:2 X:dpERK" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Grk:dpERK:1 S:dpERK:1 X:dpERK" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Grk:dpERK:1 S:dpERK:2" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Grk:dpERK:1 S:dpERK:2 X:dpERK" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" A:dpERK Grk:dpERK:1 S:dpERK:1 X:dpERK" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" A:dpERK Grk:dpERK:1 S:dpERK:2 X:dpERK" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" S:dpERK:2" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" S:dpERK:2 X:dpERK" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" A:dpERK S:dpERK:2 X:dpERK" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Grk:dpERK:2" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Grk:dpERK:2 S:dpERK:1" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" A:dpERK Grk:dpERK:2" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" A:dpERK Grk:dpERK:2 S:dpERK:1" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" A:dpERK Grk:dpERK:2 S:dpERK:2" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Grk:dpERK:1 X:dpERK" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Grk:dpERK:1 S:dpERK:1" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" A:dpERK Grk:dpERK:1 X:dpERK" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" A:dpERK Grk:dpERK:1 S:dpERK:1" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" A:dpERK Grk:dpERK:1 S:dpERK:2" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" S:dpERK:1" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" S:dpERK:1 X:dpERK" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" A:dpERK S:dpERK:1 X:dpERK" val="1"/>
  <value val="2">
    <exp str="Grk:3"/>
    <exp str="Grk:2 &amp; ((S:2 &amp; !A) | X)"/>
    <exp str="Grk:1 &amp; ((S:2 &amp; !A) | (S &amp; X))"/>
    <exp str="!Grk &amp; S:2 &amp; (!A | X)"/>
  </value>
  <value val="1">
    <exp str="Grk:2 &amp; ((S:2 &amp; A &amp; !X) | (!S:2 &amp; !X))"/>
    <exp str="Grk:1 &amp; ((S:2 &amp; A &amp; !X) | (S:1 &amp; !X) | (!S &amp; X))"/>
    <exp str="!Grk &amp; S:1 &amp; (!A | X)"/>
  </value>
  <annotation>
    <comment>Activation of the EGF pathway may be visualized directly through dpERK activation, starting from a midline-centered pattern, which expands to encompass a larger part of the dorsal-anterior domain, before regressing to a spectacle-like pattern and finally to the L-shape pattern characteristic of the  floor domain (Wasserman and Freeman, 1998; Peri et al., 1999; Nakamura and Matsuno, 2003; Zartman et al., 2009).
</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<rect x="180" y="270" width="71" height="25" backgroundColor="#000000" foregroundColor="#ffffff"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="Mid" maxvalue="1">
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" earlyGrk:Mid" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Mid:Mid earlyGrk:Mid" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Mid:Mid" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Mid:Mid earlyDpp:Mid" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Mid:Mid earlyDpp:Mid earlyGrk:Mid" val="1"/>
  <value val="1">
    <exp str="(earlyGrk &amp; !earlyDpp) | Mid"/>
  </value>
  <annotation>
    <comment>Midline expression marks the posterior domain of the follicular epithelium (Fregoso Lomas et al., 2013)</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="310" y="128" width="71" height="25" backgroundColor="#ccffcc" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="Mirr" maxvalue="1">
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" dpERK:Mirr" val="1"/>
  <value val="1">
    <exp str="dpERK &amp; !Mid"/>
  </value>
  <annotation>
    <comment>Transcription factor Mirror. Mirr is activated in a large dorsal-anterior patch of the epithelium by low levels of EGFR activity (Jordan et al., 2000; Zhao et al., 2000a; Shravage et al., 2007).
</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="284" y="331" width="55" height="25" backgroundColor="#000000" foregroundColor="#ffffff"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="Rho" maxvalue="2">
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" dpERK:Rho:2 Mirr:Rho" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" dpERK:Rho:1 Mirr:Rho" val="1"/>
  <value val="2">
    <exp str="!Br &amp; Mirr &amp; dpERK:2"/>
  </value>
  <value val="1">
    <exp str="!Br &amp; Mirr &amp; dpERK:1"/>
  </value>
  <annotation>
    <comment>Rho expression pattern seems to correlate with EGFR activity as it evolves from the whole dorsal-anterior region in early stages to the characteristic one-cell wide floor region, adjacent to the roof, in  late stages (Ruohola-Baker et al., 1993; Neuman-Silberberg and Schupbach, 1994; Hsu et al., 1996; Queenan et al., 1997). Rhomboid activates
Spitz, which is then secreted (Urban et al., 2001, Lee et al., 2001).
</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<rect x="350" y="492" width="55" height="25" backgroundColor="#3333ff" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="Br_adj" maxvalue="1" input="true">
  <annotation>
    <comment>Denotes Br expression in neighboring cells.</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="650" y="590" width="60" height="25" backgroundColor="#ffffff" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="S" maxvalue="2">
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Rho:S:2" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Rho_ext:S:1 Rho:S:2" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Rho_ext:S:2 Rho:S:2" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Rho_ext:S:2" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Rho_ext:S:2 Rho:S:1" val="2"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Rho:S:1" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Rho_ext:S:1 Rho:S:1" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Rho_ext:S:1" val="1"/>
  <value val="2">
    <exp str="Rho:2 | Rho_ext:2"/>
  </value>
  <value val="1">
    <exp str="(Rho:1 | Rho_ext:1) &amp; !(Rho:2 | Rho_ext:2)"/>
  </value>
  <annotation>
    <comment>S combines the values of Rho and Rho ext, to account for Spitz signalling.</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<rect x="508" y="484" width="35" height="25" backgroundColor="#cccccc" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="Aos_ext" maxvalue="2" input="true">
  <annotation>
    <comment>Denotes Aos expression in neighboring cells.

</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<rect x="650" y="431" width="60" height="25" backgroundColor="#ffffff" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="earlyDpp" maxvalue="1" input="true">
  <annotation>
    <comment>dpp expression is first detectable at the end of stage 8 in approximately 20 to 30 somatic follicle cells at the anterior tip of the egg chamber (Twombly et al., 1996). Moreover, there is evidence that BMP pathway is active in early (stege 6) egg chambers (Chen and Schupbach, 2006).</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="268" y="70" width="70" height="25" backgroundColor="#ff99ff" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="Pnt" maxvalue="1">
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" dpERK:Pnt" val="1"/>
  <value val="1">
    <exp str="dpERK"/>
  </value>
  <annotation>
    <comment>Transcription factor Pointed. At stage 10A, it is expressed along the dorsal midline, and in the roof region at stages 10B-11 (Morimoto et al., 1996; Yakoby et al., 2008a).
</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="149" y="430" width="55" height="25" backgroundColor="#000000" foregroundColor="#ffffff"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="Br" maxvalue="1">
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Mirr:Br" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Br:Br Mirr:Br" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Br:Br" val="1"/>
  <value val="1">
    <exp str="(Mirr | Br) &amp; !Dpp &amp; !Pnt"/>
  </value>
  <annotation>
    <comment>Broad-Complex (Br-C), is a transcription factor. It is a key marker of the roof region, expressed in two large patches of cells on each side of the dorsal midline (Deng and Bownes, 1997; Tzolovsky et al., 1999; Dequier et al., 2001; Ward and Berg, 2005; Chen and Schupbach, 2006; Yakoby et al., 2008a; Boisclair Lachance et al., 2009; Zartman et al., 2009). Broad mRNA is initially present at low levels everywhere, then repressed in an antero-dorsal T-shaped domain, before increasing in the roof domains and finally decreasing everywhere else.

Br expression is controlled by two promoters (Fuchs et al., 2012); only the BrL promoter is considered here.
</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="174" y="571" width="55" height="25" backgroundColor="#ff3333" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="Grk" maxvalue="3" input="true">
  <annotation>
    <comment>Gurken is a TGF-α like protein secreted by the oocyte. Accumulates around the oocyte nucleus in the dorsal-anterior corner from stage 8 (Neuman-Silberberg and Schupbach, 1994; Neuman-Silberberg and Schupbach, 1996). Signals to the overlying follicular epithelium until the formation of the vitelline membrane at stage 10B (Wasserman and Freeman, 1998).
</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<rect x="170" y="131" width="60" height="25" backgroundColor="#ffcc00" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="Aos" maxvalue="1">
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" dpERK:Aos Pnt:Aos" val="1"/>
  <value val="1">
    <exp str="Pnt &amp; !Mid &amp; dpERK"/>
  </value>
  <annotation>
    <comment>Argos expression begins around stage 10A in the dorsal centripetal follicle cells, before extending to the dorsal midline. The patch splits around stage 11-12 into a pattern reminiscent of the late pattern of Rho (Queenan et al., 1997; Wasserman and Freeman, 1998; Peri et al., 1999; Nakamura and Matsuno, 2003).
</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="339" y="425" width="55" height="25" backgroundColor="#000000" foregroundColor="#ffffff"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="A" maxvalue="1">
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Aos_ext:A:2" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Aos_ext:A:2 Aos:A" val="1"/>
  <parameter idActiveInteractions=" Aos_ext:A:1 Aos:A" val="1"/>
  <value val="1">
    <exp str="Aos_ext:2 | (Aos &amp; Aos_ext:1)"/>
  </value>
  <annotation>
    <comment>A combines the values of Aos and Aos ext.</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="559" y="432" width="35" height="25" backgroundColor="#cccccc" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
<node id="Dpp" maxvalue="1" input="true">
  <annotation>
    <comment>Decapentaplegic is a TGF-β superfamily member, secreted from the stretched FCs that overlay the nurse cells, and from stage 10 onwards in the centripetally migrating follicle cells (Twombly et al., 1996). Signals to the follicular epithelium through the receptor Tkv.

At stage 10, Dpp/Tkv activity can be detected in a narrow band along the anterior border of the follicular epithelium, slightly larger at the dorsal side (Deng and Bownes, 1997; Yakoby et al., 2008b).
</comment>
  </annotation>

			<nodevisualsetting>
				<ellipse x="100" y="130" width="60" height="25" backgroundColor="#9933ff" foregroundColor="#000000"/>
			</nodevisualsetting>
</node>
		<edge id="earlyGrk:Mid" from="earlyGrk" to="Mid" minvalue="1" sign="positive">
<annotation>
  <comment>early, posterio Grk signalling activates Mid expressin (Fregoso Lomas et al., 2013)</comment>
</annotation>
			<edgevisualsetting>
				<polyline points="392,82 370,110 345,140" line_style="straight" line_color="#00cc00" line_width="2" routage="auto"/>
			</edgevisualsetting>
		</edge>
		<edge id="X:dpERK" from="X" to="dpERK" minvalue="1" sign="positive">
<annotation>
  <comment>hypothetical enhancement of EGFR activity via a juxtacrine signal from the roof.</comment>
</annotation>
			<edgevisualsetting>
				<polyline points="479,600 480,230 240,230 215,282" line_style="straight" line_color="#00cc00" line_width="2" routage="auto"/>
			</edgevisualsetting>
		</edge>
		<edge id="Rho_ext:S:1" from="Rho_ext" to="S" minvalue="1" maxvalue="1" sign="positive">
<annotation>
  <comment>Rho activates Spitz, which is then secreted (Lee et al., 2001; Urban et al., 2001)

Lee et al., 2001
Regulated intracellular ligand transport and proteolysis control EGF signal activation in Drosophila.
Cell 107(2):161-71
pubmed:11672524


******************
Rule for the epithelial model:
Rho:2: autocrine or at least 6 cells over six neighbours
(self.parentcell.getspecies('Rho').value==1 or self.parentcell.haswith('Rho', distance=(1,1))&gt;=6)


Rho:1: between 2 and 5 cells among 6 neighbours:
(self.parentcell.getspecies('Rho').value==0 and self.parentcell.haswith('Rho', distance=(1,1))&gt;=2 and self.parentcell.haswith('Rho', distance=(1,1))&lt;6)


Rho:
(self.parentcell.getspecies('Rho').value==1 or self.parentcell.haswith('Rho', distance=(1,1))&gt;=2)</comment>
</annotation>
			<edgevisualsetting>
				<polyline points="680,502 590,500 525,496" line_style="straight" line_color="#00cc00" line_width="2" routage="auto"/>
			</edgevisualsetting>
		</edge>
		<edge id="Rho_ext:S:2" from="Rho_ext" to="S" minvalue="2" sign="positive">
			<edgevisualsetting>
				<polyline points="680,502 590,500 525,496" line_style="straight" line_color="#00cc00" line_width="2" routage="auto"/>
			</edgevisualsetting>
		</edge>
		<edge id="dpERK:Rho:1" from="dpERK" to="Rho" minvalue="1" maxvalue="1" sign="positive">
<annotation>
  <comment>rho transcription is repressed by the transcription factor CF2 (Hsu et al., 1996); CF2 is downregulated by the EGFR pathway (Mantrova and  Hsu, 1998)</comment>
</annotation>
			<edgevisualsetting>
				<polyline points="215,282 220,510 377,504" line_style="straight" line_color="#00cc00" line_width="2" routage="auto"/>
			</edgevisualsetting>
		</edge>
		<edge id="dpERK:Rho:2" from="dpERK" to="Rho" minvalue="2" sign="positive">
			<edgevisualsetting>
				<polyline points="215,282 220,510 377,504" line_style="straight" line_color="#00cc00" line_width="2" routage="auto"/>
			</edgevisualsetting>
		</edge>
		<edge id="dpERK:Pnt" from="dpERK" to="Pnt" minvalue="2" sign="positive">
<annotation>
  <comment>Pnt is activated by high levels of EGFR activity (Morimoto et al., 1996; Deng and Bownes,
1997; Chang et al., 2003).</comment>
</annotation>
			<edgevisualsetting>
				<polyline points="215,282 190,360 176,442" line_style="straight" line_color="#00cc00" line_width="2" routage="auto"/>
			</edgevisualsetting>
		</edge>
		<edge id="dpERK:Mirr" from="dpERK" to="Mirr" minvalue="1" sign="positive">
<annotation>
  <comment>Activation in a large dorsal-anterior patch of the epithelium by low levels of EGFR activity, through Cic (Jordan et al., 2000; Zhao et al., 2000b; Shravage et al., 2007).



</comment>
</annotation>
			<edgevisualsetting>
				<polyline points="215,282 240,340 311,343" line_style="straight" line_color="#00cc00" line_width="2" routage="auto"/>
			</edgevisualsetting>
		</edge>
		<edge id="dpERK:Aos" from="dpERK" to="Aos" minvalue="1" sign="positive">
<annotation>
  <comment>In addition to Argos expression pattern, we have that in intervein cells in the wing imaginal disk, aos transcription is repressed by Cic in a cell autonomous way; Cic itself is downregulated by EGFR (Roch et al., 2002; Atkey et al., 2006; Astigarraga et al., 2007; Yakoby et al., 2008b).</comment>
</annotation>
			<edgevisualsetting>
				<polyline points="215,282 230,430 366,437" line_style="straight" line_color="#00cc00" line_width="2" routage="auto"/>
			</edgevisualsetting>
		</edge>
		<edge id="Mid:Mirr" from="Mid" to="Mirr" minvalue="1" sign="negative">
<annotation>
  <comment>Mid represses Mirr and its target Br (Fregoso Lomas et al., 2013)</comment>
</annotation>
			<edgevisualsetting>
				<polyline points="345,140 320,250 311,343" line_style="straight" line_color="#cc0000" line_width="2" routage="auto"/>
			</edgevisualsetting>
		</edge>
		<edge id="Mid:Aos" from="Mid" to="Aos" minvalue="1" sign="negative">
<annotation>
  <comment>When EGFR is ectopically activated in the epithelium, Argos transcription is restricted to the anterior side (Queenan et al., 1997), which suggests repression by Mid.
</comment>
</annotation>
			<edgevisualsetting>
				<polyline points="345,140 370,270 366,437" line_style="straight" line_color="#cc0000" line_width="2" routage="auto"/>
			</edgevisualsetting>
		</edge>
		<edge id="Mid:Mid" from="Mid" to="Mid" minvalue="1" sign="positive">
			<edgevisualsetting>
				<polyline points="345,140 335,111 345,107 355,111 345,140" line_style="curve" line_color="#666666" pattern="dash" line_width="2" routage="auto"/>
			</edgevisualsetting>
		</edge>
		<edge id="Mirr:Rho" from="Mirr" to="Rho" minvalue="1" sign="positive">
<annotation>
  <comment>Ectopic expression of mirr induces ectopic Rho expression (Jordan et al., 2000, 2005).

There is evidence that some anterior clue, likely Dpp, is required to activate Rho (Queenan et al., 1997; Peri and Roth, 2000, Ward and Berg, 2005), and mirror could relay that signal to Rho.


</comment>
</annotation>
			<edgevisualsetting>
				<polyline points="311,343 310,500 377,504" line_style="straight" line_color="#00cc00" line_width="2" routage="auto"/>
			</edgevisualsetting>
		</edge>
		<edge id="Mirr:Br" from="Mirr" to="Br" minvalue="1" sign="positive">
<annotation>
  <comment>Mirr is required both to upregulate Br-C in the normal appendage primordium, and to downregulate it in the T region (Boisclair-Lachance, 2009). Fuchs et al., 2012, showed that Mirr activates the BrL promoter (late, Roof-specific Br pattern) and represses the BrE promoter (Early, dorsal-anterior Br pattern).</comment>
</annotation>
			<edgevisualsetting>
				<polyline points="311,343 300,580 201,583" line_style="straight" line_color="#00cc00" line_width="2" routage="auto"/>
			</edgevisualsetting>
		</edge>
		<edge id="Rho:S:1" from="Rho" to="S" minvalue="1" maxvalue="1" sign="positive">
<annotation>
  <comment>Rho activates Spitz, which is then secreted (Lee et al., 2001; Urban et al., 2001)</comment>
</annotation>
			<edgevisualsetting>
				<polyline points="377,504 440,500 525,496" line_style="straight" line_color="#00cc00" line_width="2" routage="auto"/>
			</edgevisualsetting>
		</edge>
		<edge id="Rho:S:2" from="Rho" to="S" minvalue="2" sign="positive">
			<edgevisualsetting>
				<polyline points="377,504 440,500 525,496" line_style="straight" line_color="#00cc00" line_width="2" routage="auto"/>
			</edgevisualsetting>
		</edge>
		<edge id="Br_adj:X" from="Br_adj" to="X" minvalue="1" sign="positive">
<annotation>
  <comment>Hypothetical mechanism. EGFR activity seems to be enhanced in cells in contact with the roof region. Br is taken as a marker of the roof.</comment>
</annotation>
			<edgevisualsetting>
				<polyline points="680,602 570,600 479,600" line_style="straight" line_color="#00cc00" line_width="2" routage="auto"/>
			</edgevisualsetting>
		</edge>
		<edge id="S:dpERK:1" from="S" to="dpERK" minvalue="1" maxvalue="1" sign="positive">
<annotation>
  <comment>Secreted Spitz activates EGFR (Rutledge et al., 1992; Lee et al., 2001; Urban et al., 2001).



</comment>
</annotation>
			<edgevisualsetting>
				<polyline points="525,496 530,210 230,210 215,282" line_style="straight" line_color="#00cc00" line_width="2" routage="auto"/>
			</edgevisualsetting>
		</edge>
		<edge id="S:dpERK:2" from="S" to="dpERK" minvalue="2" sign="positive">
			<edgevisualsetting>
