<annotation>
  <comment>There is indirect evidence that Dpp set the posterior boundary of the appendage primordia (Queenan et al., 1997; Ward and Berg, 2005; Shravage et al., 2007). Considering the contrasting results of BMP pathway disruption on br expression (Peri and Roth 2000, Shravage et al., 2007, Yakoby et al. 2008b, Marmion et al., 2013), we postulate that an early BMP signal inhibits Midline.</comment>
</annotation>
